The plot F0/F versus Hg2+ concentration (Stern-Volmer plots) is shown in Fig. 4B, where F0 and F are fluorescence intensities in the absence and presence of Hg2+, respectively. Linear behavior was observed in the range of 0.01–50μM (F0/F=0.0112 CHg (μM)+1.067; R2
                        =0.96). Detection limit was 8nM based on equation LOD=3σ/s (σ is the standard deviation of blank (n=5) and s is the slope of the calibration curve). Linear range and detection limit of proposed sensor were compared with other Hg2+ fluorescence sensors (Table 1
                        ). This sensor was comparable with CdTe and CdS QDs sensors [25,27]. In comparison with CdS/ZnS/As [23], vinyl phosphonic acid [1] and N,S/C-dots [19] sensors, this sensor had lower detection limit, but detection limit of graphitic carbon nitride sensor [2] was lower. Simple and green synthesis, solubility in water, no need to any organic solvent and fast response time were good properties of the new sensor.
